cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.DC 

The paper focuses on authentication protocols for the Internet of Things (IoT), which involves communication and networking technologies. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses threat models and formal security verification techniques, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
